{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":685,"text":"The urban explosion"},{"time":3727,"text":"of the last years of economic boom"},{"time":7952,"text":"also produced dramatic marginalization,"},{"time":11463,"text":"resulting in the explosion of slums"},{"time":13737,"text":"in many parts of the world."},{"time":16352,"text":"This polarization of enclaves of mega-wealth"},{"time":19599,"text":"surrounded by sectors of poverty"},{"time":22434,"text":"and the socioeconomic inequalities\nthey have engendered"},{"time":25816,"text":"is really at the center of today's urban crisis."},{"time":29378,"text":"But I want to begin tonight"},{"time":31736,"text":"by suggesting that this urban crisis"},{"time":34174,"text":"is not only economic or environmental."},{"time":38054,"text":"It's particularly a cultural crisis,"},{"time":40952,"text":"a crisis of the institutions"},{"time":43837,"text":"unable to reimagine the stupid ways"},{"time":47573,"text":"which we have been growing,"},{"time":49997,"text":"unable to challenge the oil-hungry,"},{"time":53310,"text":"selfish urbanization that have perpetuated"},{"time":57067,"text":"cities based on consumption,"},{"time":59529,"text":"from southern California to New York to Dubai."},{"time":64960,"text":"So I just really want to share with you a reflection"},{"time":68958,"text":"that the future of cities today"},{"time":71298,"text":"depends less on buildings"},{"time":73989,"text":"and, in fact, depends more"},{"time":76404,"text":"on the fundamental reorganization\nof socioeconomic relations,"},{"time":81154,"text":"that the best ideas in the shaping"},{"time":83158,"text":"of the city in the future"},{"time":84988,"text":"will not come from enclaves of economic power"},{"time":89037,"text":"and abundance,"},{"time":90415,"text":"but in fact from sectors of conflict and scarcity"},{"time":96046,"text":"from which an urgent imagination"},{"time":98886,"text":"can really inspire us to rethink urban growth today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":102910,"text":"And let me illustrate what I mean"},{"time":106490,"text":"by understanding or engaging sites of conflict"},{"time":110395,"text":"as harboring creativity, as I briefly introduce you"},{"time":114476,"text":"to the Tijuana-San Diego border region,"},{"time":117009,"text":"which has been the laboratory to\nrethink my practice as an architect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":121214,"text":"This is the wall, the border wall,"},{"time":123726,"text":"that separates San Diego and Tijuana,"},{"time":126237,"text":"Latin America and the United States,"},{"time":129078,"text":"a physical emblem"},{"time":131115,"text":"of exclusionary planning policies"},{"time":133765,"text":"that have perpetuated the division"},{"time":136276,"text":"of communities, jurisdictions"},{"time":138709,"text":"and resources across the world."},{"time":141844,"text":"In this border region, we find"},{"time":144547,"text":"some of the wealthiest real estate,"},{"time":146964,"text":"as I once found in the edges of San Diego,"},{"time":149431,"text":"barely 20 minutes away"},{"time":151655,"text":"from some of the poorest \nsettlements in Latin America."},{"time":155781,"text":"And while these two cities have the same population,"},{"time":159144,"text":"San Diego has grown six times larger than Tijuana"},{"time":162980,"text":"in the last decades,"},{"time":164742,"text":"immediately thrusting us to confront"},{"time":168132,"text":"the tensions and conflicts"},{"time":170179,"text":"between sprawl and density,"},{"time":171927,"text":"which are at the center of today's discussion"},{"time":173918,"text":"about environmental sustainability."},{"time":176746,"text":"So I've been arguing in the last years"},{"time":179478,"text":"that, in fact, the slums of Tijuana can teach a lot"},{"time":183183,"text":"to the sprawls of San Diego"},{"time":184844,"text":"when it comes to socioeconomic sustainability,"},{"time":188374,"text":"that we should pay attention and learn"},{"time":190793,"text":"from the many migrant communities"},{"time":193106,"text":"on both sides of this border wall"},{"time":195621,"text":"so that we can translate their informal processes"},{"time":198958,"text":"of urbanization."}]},{"cues":[{"time":201017,"text":"What do I mean by the informal in this case?"},{"time":204139,"text":"I'm really just talking about"},{"time":205967,"text":"the compendium of social practices of adaptation"},{"time":209623,"text":"that enable many of these migrant communities"},{"time":212462,"text":"to transgress imposed political and economic recipes"},{"time":217016,"text":"of urbanization."},{"time":218569,"text":"I'm talking simply about the creative intelligence"},{"time":221819,"text":"of the bottom-up,"},{"time":224194,"text":"whether manifested in the slums of Tijuana"},{"time":227391,"text":"that build themselves, in fact,\nwith the waste of San Diego,"},{"time":231135,"text":"or the many migrant neighborhoods\nin Southern California"},{"time":233893,"text":"that have begun to be retrofitted with difference"},{"time":236969,"text":"in the last decades."}]},{"cues":[{"time":238626,"text":"So I've been interested as an artist"},{"time":240834,"text":"in the measuring, the observation,"},{"time":243418,"text":"of many of the trans-border informal flows"},{"time":245690,"text":"across this border:"},{"time":247380,"text":"in one direction, from south to north,"},{"time":249817,"text":"the flow of immigrants into the United States,"},{"time":252410,"text":"and from north to south the flow of waste"},{"time":255419,"text":"from southern California into Tijuana."},{"time":258450,"text":"I'm referring to the recycling"},{"time":260718,"text":"of these old post-war bungalows"},{"time":264170,"text":"that Mexican contractors bring to the border"},{"time":267629,"text":"as American developers are disposing of them"},{"time":270474,"text":"in the process of building a more inflated version"},{"time":273042,"text":"of suburbia in the last decades."},{"time":275118,"text":"So these are houses waiting to cross the border."},{"time":278033,"text":"Not only people cross the border here,"},{"time":280385,"text":"but entire chunks of one city move to the next,"},{"time":283652,"text":"and when these houses are placed\non top of these steel frames,"},{"time":287546,"text":"they leave the first floor to become the second"},{"time":290123,"text":"to be in-filled with more house,"},{"time":292177,"text":"with a small business."},{"time":293835,"text":"This layering of spaces and economies"},{"time":296712,"text":"is very interesting to notice."},{"time":298994,"text":"But not only houses, also small debris"},{"time":301509,"text":"from one city, from San Diego, to Tijuana."},{"time":303856,"text":"Probably a lot of you have seen the rubber tires"},{"time":306242,"text":"that are used in the slums to build retaining walls."},{"time":308871,"text":"But look at what people have done here in conditions"},{"time":311224,"text":"of socioeconomic emergency."},{"time":313452,"text":"They have figured out how to peel off the tire,"},{"time":316613,"text":"how to thread it and interlock it"},{"time":318978,"text":"to construct a more efficient retaining wall."},{"time":323106,"text":"Or the garage doors that are brought"},{"time":326318,"text":"from San Diego in trucks"},{"time":328826,"text":"to become the new skin of emergency housing"},{"time":333555,"text":"in many of these slums"},{"time":335394,"text":"surrounding the edges of Tijuana."}]},{"cues":[{"time":337724,"text":"So while, as an architect,"},{"time":339140,"text":"this is a very compelling thing to witness,"},{"time":341067,"text":"this creative intelligence,"},{"time":342761,"text":"I also want to keep myself in check."},{"time":344774,"text":"I don't want to romanticize poverty."},{"time":346810,"text":"I just want to suggest"},{"time":348801,"text":"that this informal urbanization"},{"time":350942,"text":"is not just the image of precariousness,"},{"time":354541,"text":"that informality here, the informal,"},{"time":357623,"text":"is really a set of socioeconomic\nand political procedures"},{"time":362153,"text":"that we could translate as artists,"},{"time":364862,"text":"that this is about a bottom-up urbanization"},{"time":367207,"text":"that performs."},{"time":368732,"text":"See here, buildings are not important"},{"time":371558,"text":"just for their looks,"},{"time":373521,"text":"but, in fact, they are important for what they can do."},{"time":376962,"text":"They truly perform as they transform through time"},{"time":380076,"text":"and as communities negotiate"},{"time":382224,"text":"the spaces and boundaries and resources."}]},{"cues":[{"time":385733,"text":"So while waste flows southbound,"},{"time":388854,"text":"people go north in search of dollars,"},{"time":391382,"text":"and most of my research has had to do"},{"time":393917,"text":"with the impact of immigration"},{"time":397812,"text":"in the alteration of the homogeneity"},{"time":400286,"text":"of many neighborhoods in the United States,"},{"time":402612,"text":"particularly in San Diego."},{"time":404576,"text":"And I'm talking about how this begins to suggest"},{"time":406961,"text":"that the future of Southern California"},{"time":409614,"text":"depends on the retrofitting"},{"time":412137,"text":"of the large urbanization -- I mean, on steroids --"},{"time":415344,"text":"with the small programs,"},{"time":417832,"text":"social and economic."},{"time":419608,"text":"I'm referring to how immigrants,"},{"time":421713,"text":"when they come to these neighborhoods,"},{"time":423511,"text":"they begin to alter the one-dimensionality"},{"time":426562,"text":"of parcels and properties"},{"time":428544,"text":"into more socially and\neconomically complex systems,"},{"time":432931,"text":"as they begin to plug an\ninformal economy into a garage,"},{"time":436668,"text":"or as they build an illegal granny flat"},{"time":438982,"text":"to support an extended family."},{"time":441484,"text":"This socioeconomic entrepreneurship"},{"time":446559,"text":"on the ground within these neighborhoods"},{"time":449662,"text":"really begins to suggest ways of translating that"},{"time":453208,"text":"into new, inclusive and more equitable"},{"time":457355,"text":"land use policies."},{"time":459394,"text":"So many stories emerge from these dynamics"},{"time":462125,"text":"of alteration of space,"},{"time":464986,"text":"such as &amp;quot;the informal Buddha,&amp;quot;"},{"time":466834,"text":"which tells the story of a small house"},{"time":469407,"text":"that saved itself, it did not travel to Mexico,"},{"time":472408,"text":"but it was retrofitted in the end"},{"time":474412,"text":"into a Buddhist temple,"},{"time":476662,"text":"and in so doing,"},{"time":477891,"text":"this small house transforms or mutates"},{"time":481147,"text":"from a singular dwelling"},{"time":482845,"text":"into a small, or a micro, socioeconomic"},{"time":485667,"text":"and cultural infrastructure inside a neighborhood."}]},{"cues":[{"time":489623,"text":"So these action neighborhoods, as I call them,"},{"time":492370,"text":"really become the inspiration"},{"time":494398,"text":"to imagine other interpretations of citizenship"},{"time":497794,"text":"that have less to do, in fact,"},{"time":499974,"text":"with belonging to the nation-state,"},{"time":501956,"text":"and more with upholding the notion of citizenship"},{"time":505802,"text":"as a creative act"},{"time":507696,"text":"that reorganizes institutional protocols"},{"time":510547,"text":"in the spaces of the city."}]},{"cues":[{"time":512877,"text":"As an artist, I've been interested, in fact,"},{"time":515732,"text":"in the visualization of citizenship,"},{"time":518461,"text":"the gathering of many anecdotes, urban stories,"},{"time":522026,"text":"in order to narrativize the relationship"},{"time":525094,"text":"between social processes and spaces."},{"time":528224,"text":"This is a story of a group of teenagers"},{"time":531343,"text":"that one night, a few months ago,"},{"time":534266,"text":"decided to invade this space under the freeway"},{"time":537198,"text":"to begin constructing their own skateboard park."},{"time":540412,"text":"With shovels in hand, they started to dig."},{"time":543553,"text":"Two weeks later, the police stopped them."},{"time":546410,"text":"They barricaded the place,"},{"time":548111,"text":"and the teenagers were evicted,"},{"time":550063,"text":"and the teenagers decided to fight back,"},{"time":552776,"text":"not with bank cards or slogans"},{"time":555243,"text":"but with constructing a critical process."},{"time":557996,"text":"The first thing they did was to recognize"},{"time":560711,"text":"the specificity of political jurisdiction"},{"time":563691,"text":"inscribed in that empty space."},{"time":566418,"text":"They found out that they had been lucky"},{"time":568496,"text":"because they had not begun to dig"},{"time":570310,"text":"under Caltrans territoy."},{"time":572693,"text":"Caltrans is a state agency that governs the freeway,"},{"time":575925,"text":"so it would have been very\ndifficult to negotiate with them."},{"time":578490,"text":"They were lucky, they said, because they began"},{"time":580370,"text":"to dig under an arm of the freeway"},{"time":582777,"text":"that belongs to the local municipality."},{"time":585040,"text":"They were also lucky, they said,"},{"time":586939,"text":"because they began to dig in a sort of"},{"time":588677,"text":"Bermuda Triangle of jurisdiction,"},{"time":591019,"text":"between port authority, airport authority,"},{"time":594496,"text":"two city districts, and a review board."},{"time":597309,"text":"All these red lines are the invisible"},{"time":600087,"text":"political institutions that were inscribed"},{"time":602665,"text":"in that leftover empty space."},{"time":605699,"text":"With this knowledge, these teenagers"},{"time":608654,"text":"as skaters confronted the city."},{"time":611337,"text":"They came to the city attorney's office."},{"time":613491,"text":"The city attorney told them"},{"time":615440,"text":"that in order to continue the negotiation"},{"time":617336,"text":"they had to become an NGO,"},{"time":619279,"text":"and of course they didn't know what an NGO was."},{"time":621540,"text":"They had to talk to their friends in Seattle"},{"time":624479,"text":"who had gone through the same experience."},{"time":626390,"text":"And they began to realize the necessity"},{"time":628574,"text":"to organize themselves even deeper"},{"time":630913,"text":"and began to fundraise, to organize budgets,"},{"time":635047,"text":"to really be aware of all the knowledge"},{"time":637371,"text":"embedded in the urban code in San Diego"},{"time":640604,"text":"so that they could begin to redefine"},{"time":642822,"text":"the very meaning of public space in the city,"},{"time":646642,"text":"expanding it to other categories."},{"time":649134,"text":"At the end, the teenagers won the case"},{"time":651769,"text":"with that evidence, and they were able"},{"time":654242,"text":"to construct their skateboard park"},{"time":656857,"text":"under that freeway."}]},{"cues":[{"time":658467,"text":"Now for many of you, this story"},{"time":660912,"text":"might seem trivial or naive."},{"time":663152,"text":"For me as an architect, it has become"},{"time":665101,"text":"a fundamental narrative,"},{"time":667439,"text":"because it begins to teach me"},{"time":669292,"text":"that this micro-community"},{"time":671247,"text":"not only designed another category of public space"},{"time":674739,"text":"but they also designed the socioeconomic protocols"},{"time":678544,"text":"that were necessary to be inscribed in that space"},{"time":681641,"text":"for its long-term sustainability."},{"time":684602,"text":"They also taught me"},{"time":686087,"text":"that similar to the migrant communities"},{"time":688122,"text":"on both sides of the border,"},{"time":689651,"text":"they engaged conflict itself as a creative tool,"},{"time":693368,"text":"because they had to produce a process"},{"time":695172,"text":"that enabled them to reorganize resources"},{"time":698789,"text":"and the politics of the city."},{"time":700623,"text":"In that act, that informal,"},{"time":703148,"text":"bottom-up act of transgression,"},{"time":705403,"text":"really began to trickle up"},{"time":707552,"text":"to transform top-down policy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":710670,"text":"Now this journey from the bottom-up"},{"time":715173,"text":"to the transformation of the top-down"},{"time":717353,"text":"is where I find hope today."},{"time":719871,"text":"And I'm thinking of how these modest alterations"},{"time":724120,"text":"with space and with policy"},{"time":727063,"text":"in many cities in the world,"},{"time":729088,"text":"in primarily the urgency"},{"time":731802,"text":"of a collective imagination"},{"time":734076,"text":"as these communities"},{"time":735550,"text":"reimagine their own forms of governance,"},{"time":737957,"text":"social organization, and infrastructure,"},{"time":740648,"text":"really is at the center"},{"time":742576,"text":"of the new formation"},{"time":744664,"text":"of democratic politics of the urban."},{"time":747976,"text":"It is, in fact, this that could become the framework"},{"time":751253,"text":"for producing new social"},{"time":754274,"text":"and economic justice in the city."},{"time":757330,"text":"I want to say this and emphasize it,"},{"time":758948,"text":"because this is the only way I see"},{"time":762597,"text":"that can enable us to move"},{"time":764810,"text":"from urbanizations of consumption"},{"time":768035,"text":"to neighborhoods of production today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":771393,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":773281,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}